            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Hello all.\r\n\r\nCouldn't look into this issue earlier, but noticed a new version of nvim Snap was released. I see nvim-treesitter was removed, as discussed with @justinmk , but I believe all treesitter parsers were also removed - and default should build include some, as Justin noticed. See error below, with new version, for instance:\r\n<img width=\"1916\" height=\"363\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/178cc5c2-0c43-4f70-a704-73297dbb0807\" />\r\n\r\nThis is after issuing \":h\" on command line. I looked into Flatpak package and, at first glance, it seems it explicitly downloads these parsers manually, though I confess I just skimmed it very briefly.\r\n\r\nTl;DR: the new package builds, but there's a new problem. I believe we should treat this on nightly before bringing to stable, for being on the safe side.\r\n\r\nWill attempt a fix, but @jcharlong is welcome to try too, if his schedule permits before mine.",
