        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It does appear that the parsers are already present within the snap. Testing with the latest v0.11.6 amd64 release & `unsquashfs`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ls\r\nnvim_v0.11.6_amd64.snap  squashfs-root\r\n$ fd parser$ --exec eza -T\r\n./squashfs-root/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/nvim/parser\r\n├── c.so\r\n├── lua.so\r\n├── markdown.so\r\n├── markdown_inline.so\r\n├── query.so\r\n├── vim.so\r\n└── vimdoc.so\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have an environment setup & can locally build to test now (at least for my native archictecture). I'll work to simply move the above directory into the directory nvim expects (i.e. `/usr/share/nvim/runtime/parser`) to see if that resolves. Barring any explanation to use `nvim-treesitter` to install parsers separately this seems like the most reasonable solution.\r\n\r\nThough also open to re-introducing the previous implementation and addressing path issues if that's preferred.",
